[2] Cholera - Angola
Date: Tue, 25 Apr 2006
From: Alfonso J. Rodriguez <ajrm_msds@yahoo.es>
Source: XinHuaNet [edited]
<http://english.people.com.cn/200604/25/eng20060425_260909.html>

WHO confirmed on Mon, 24 Apr 2006, in Luanda that cholera has claimed
860 lives and infected more than 18 000 people in Angola up to 23 Apr
2006 since it broke out there 2 months ago.
In the last 24 hours, 888 new cases including 13 deaths have been
reported in 5 out of the 18 provinces, according to a latest report
from WHO. The 5 provinces reporting cholera cases are Luanda, Bengo,
Beguela, Kwanza Norte, Kwanza Sul, according to the report.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The outbreak across most of Angola continues. A map of Angola can
be found at:
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/angola.pdf> . It
shows that all of the affected provinces are in central and western
Angola; the southern and western provinces have not reported
activity. This posting mentions Kwanza Sul (also spelled Cuanza
South or Cwanza South) although no individual reports from this
province have been reported but does not mention Malanje, which has
reported cases. - Mod.LL]

