[5] Cholera - Angola (Luanda, Malanje)
Date: Mon, 24 Apr 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Angola Press [edited]
<http://www.angolapress-angop.ao/noticia-e.asp?ID=435264>

4 more people died of cholera in Luanda, on Sat and Sun, 22 and 23
Apr 2006, increasing the number of deaths to 145, out of the 8703
cases recorded so far, Angop learned.
According to the provincial director of the Health Ministry, Vita
Vemba, the districts most affected by the illness are Sambizanga,
Cazenga, Ingombota, Viana, Kilamba Kiaxi and Rangel.
On the other hand, the number of [new?] cases has been falling in
northern Malanje province, despite isolated cases recorded in health
centers. The 1st case was recorded on 30 Mar 2006, and the illness
has already claimed 126 lives.
--
