[6] Cholera - Angola (Malanje)
Date: Mon, 24 Apr 2006
From: ProMED-mail promed@promedmail.org
Source: African News Dimension [edited]
<http://www.andnetwork.com/app?service=direct/0/Home/$StorySummary$0.$DirectLink$1&sp=l31330>

13 people, including adults and children, died of cholera in the
final hours of Thu, 20 Apr 2006, in Malanje province, making the
death toll 101.
This was revealed by the spokesman of the provincial commission for
cholera prevention and control, Andre Ribeiro, who added that the
number of cases has also gone up to 501.
Meanwhile, the health provincial director, Pedro Chagas, said the
outbreak in the province has hit 5 municipalities, including the
chief municipality.
--
