[7] Cholera - Angola (Uije)
Date: Sun, 23 Apr 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Angola Press [edited]
<http://www.angolapress-angop.ao/noticia-e.asp?ID=434965>

The provincial department of the Health Ministry in Angola's northern
Uije province is out of stocks of medicines to fight an eventual
outbreak of cholera in the region.
This was announced by the head of Public Health of the provincial
department, Jose da Cunha Mayelano, who added that in terms of
logistics, the sector has no medicines or bio-security material for
the staff. Speaking to Angop, he also said that the sector is in need
of transport to drive social mobilization teams around the province.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[It can be inferred that there have been cases of cholera in Uije,
which quickly depleted therapeutic stocks; but whether cholera is
actually present in Uije is not clearly stated. - Mod.LL]
