[8] Cholera - Angola (Kwanza Norte)
Date: Fri, 21 Apr 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: AllAfrica.com and Angola Press Agency (Luanda)[edited]
<http://allafrica.com/stories/200604210213.html>

Over the last 24 hours, 17 new cases of cholera have been recorded at
Dondo hospital, in Angola's northern Kwanza-Norte province, raising
the [number of cases] to 68 since the outbreak of the illness in the
district began on 8 Apr 2006.
The Hospital's clinical director, Joao Mendes, said 4 people have
already died in the town, 3 of them at home. As of the morning of 21
Apr 2006, 16 patients with cholera were newly admitted to the hospital.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
