[9] Cholera - Uganda (Kitgum)
Date: Thu, 27 Apr 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: AllAfrica.com and The Monitor (Kampala) [edited]
<http://allafrica.com/stories/200604260825.html>

The number of cholera victims in Agoro IDP camp in Kitgum District
has reached 73 since the epidemic broke out more than a week ago.
The Medical Officer in-charge of Lamwo Health Centre, Dr Charles
Oyoo, told Daily Monitor on Mon, 24 Apr 2006, that only 18 cases out
of the 73 were still being cared for in the isolation tent donated by
Unicef at Agoro Health Centre III. He said 10 of those were still on
intravenous fluids, while 8 were on ORS [oral rehydration salts -
Mod.MPP]. Oyoo said the rest of the victims were discharged at
various times last week but that 2 of them were re-admitted on Sun,
26 Apr 2006.
Oyoo said they were not yet sure if the cholera spread from southern
Sudan as reported by the media last week. Agoro is 50 miles from
Kitgum town and borders Sudan.
[Byline: Jimmy Kwo]
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The map of Uganda at
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/uganda.pdf> shows
the border between the northern district of Kitgum and the Sudan. - Mod.LL]
