[10] Cholera - Uganda (Arua)
Date: Wed, 26 Apr 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: African News Dimension [edited]
<http://www.andnetwork.com/index?service=direct/0/Africa/$StorySummary$4.titleStory&sp=l31690>

So far 3 residents of Maracha County in Arua, Uganda have reportedly
died of cholera, 2 weeks after the epidemic was first registered in
the locality.
The Daily Monitor has learnt that the abdominal infection has caused
64 people to be admitted to Ovujjo Health Centre III, which has been
evacuated to make room for victims of the contagious disease. Some
of the patients are said to be in a critical state. Specimen test
results from the Entebbe-based Uganda Virus Research Institute show
that the type of cholera that has so far ravaged 6 parishes in 4
different sub-counties of Maracha County is the Inaba variety.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[A map of Uganda showing Arua in the northwestern part of the country
can be found at:
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/uganda.pdf> - Mod. LL]
