[11] Cholera - Cameroon (Centre)
Date: Sun, 23 Apr 2006
From: ProMED-mail promed@promedmail.org
Source: XinHuaNet [edited]
<http://english.people.com.cn/200604/23/eng20060423_260479.html>

A recent outbreak of cholera near the Cameroonian capital of Yaounde
has killed at least 10 people, Cameroonian health authorities said on
Fri, 21 Apr 2006. Since the latest resurgence of the disease in
Bafoussam, 300 km northwest of Yaounde several weeks ago, more than
50 people had contracted the disease, suffering from vomiting and
diarrhea, health officials said.
The beginning of the year as well as Apr and May are the rainy
seasons in the West African country, during which cholera is most active.
In Feb 2006, an outbreak of cholera in Akonolinga, 40 km east of
Yaounde, claimed 8 lives. In the 15 months between Jan 2004 and Apr
2006, up to 8500 people nationwide contracted the disease, with 174
of them dead.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The map of Cameroon at
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/cameroon.pdf> shows
the location of Yaounde in Centra province of south-central Cameroon
with Akonolinga to its east. - Mod.LL]
