[12] Cholera - Tanzania (Dar es Salaam)
Date: Sun, 23 Apr 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: XinHuaNet [edited]
<http://english.people.com.cn/200604/23/eng20060423_260481.html>

The Tanzanian health ministry has revised the number of cholera
deaths in Dar es Salaam to 50 from 30 since the pandemic broke out in
December 2005. Health Minister David Mwakyusa said that at least 4244
people had contracted the disease so far.
Hygiene regarding drinking water and food is deemed key to fending
off the spread of the disease in the municipality. Local health
officials are warning people against buying and drinking water or
fruit juice packed in small plastic bags that are stored away in
buckets with ice cubes.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The map of Tanzania at
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/tanzania.pdf> shows
the capital city of Dar es Salaam on the coast south of the islands
of Zanzibar where cholera is also present. - Mod.LL]
